By ChitterSync

The Simplest Solution to a Universal Game Hub

ChitterSync: LaunchPad offers the Ability to put all your favorite games on one launcher so no having to run a different launcher each time you want to play a game

# Features

- Unified Game Library: Access all your games from a single launcher.
- Cross-Platform Support: Play games from various platforms without switching launchers.
- Customizable Interface: Personalize your gaming experience with themes and layouts.
- Automatic Updates: Keep your games up-to-date effortlessly.
- Social Integration: Connect with friends and join multiplayer sessions easily. allowing contacting friends on discord, ChitterHaven, and the game platforms
- Cloud Saves (Coming Soon): Access your game progress from any device.

# How to Install

go to [launchpad.chittersync.com/download](launchpad.chittersync.com/download#latest)

the page should automatically detect your operating system and provide the appropriate download link.

run the file and follow the on-screen instructions to complete the installation.

# Connecting Game Platforms
you will need to have each game platform installed on your computer to connect them to LaunchPad, including Steam, Epic Games Store, and others. 

Once you have the platforms installed, you can link your accounts within the LaunchPad interface. 

LaunchPad will provide download links for each platform if you do not have them installed, to access go to `settings > platforms > connected platforms` and it should list all the supported platforms.

# Troubleshooting
If you encounter any issues during installation or while connecting game platforms, please refer to the support page and contact support for assistance.

# Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)
1. **What platforms does LaunchPad support?**
   LaunchPad supports a variety of game platforms, including Steam, Epic Games Store, and more. Check the settings page for a full list of supported platforms.

2. **Can I use LaunchPad on multiple devices?**
   Yes, you can use LaunchPad on multiple devices. Just log in with your account to access your game library and settings.

3. **What should I do if a game is not showing up in LaunchPad?**
   If a game is not showing up, make sure the corresponding game platform is installed and your account is linked. You can also try refreshing the library.

4. **Is there a mobile version of LaunchPad?**
   Currently, LaunchPad is only available for desktop platforms. A mobile version for Android and iOS may be considered in the future.

5. **How can I provide feedback or report a bug?**
   You can provide feedback or report bugs through the support page. We appreciate your input to help improve LaunchPad.